defs.name: compact
defs.docs:
Set 'compact inline notation' on or off, as described for block
 [sequences](http://www.yaml.org/spec/1.2/spec.html#id2797382)
 and
 [mappings](http://www.yaml.org/spec/1.2/spec.html#id2798057).

defs.name: is_compact
defs.docs: Determine if this emitter is using 'compact inline notation'.

defs.name: Real
defs.docs:
Float types are stored as String and parsed on demand.
 Note that f64 does NOT implement Eq trait and can NOT be stored in BTreeMap.

defs.name: BadValue
defs.docs:
Accessing a nonexistent node via the Index trait returns `BadValue`. This
 simplifies error handling in the calling code. Invalid type conversion also
 returns `BadValue`.

defs.name: Yaml
defs.value: Yaml::{Real, Integer, String, Boolean, Array, Hash, Alias, Null, BadValue}
defs.docs:
A YAML node is stored as this `Yaml` enumeration, which provides an easy way to
 access your YAML document.
